Theoretical Advanced Study Institute in Elementary Particle Physics (TASI) has been held each summer since 1984, originally at Michigan, Yale, Santa Cruz, Santa Fe and Brown, and since 1989 in Boulder. Each year, typically, some sixty of the most promising advanced theory graduate students in the United States, along with a few beginning postdocs and experimental graduate students, have attended TASI.
---> http://www.colorado.edu/physics/Web/TASI_info.html

Many of today's university faculty and professional researchers are TASI alum.  This projects goal is to measure the impact TASI has on the current landscape of particle physics.
